		<div id="comment_body_65297695"><p>Quantity makes quality harder. Who would risk a massive capital investment on major projects if the chance of return was low and the risk factor high? How many people would put their heart and soul into something if there was a high risk it would just be one of many. It's like the quality of TV shows went down after cable TV. Sure we had more choices, and every niche of TV show type<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.. but at the expense of truly great TV shows and maybe even social cohesion.  You know why we were stuck with incandescent li<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
