	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65298373">Jurassic Park was made in 1994. The visual effects were stunning. Independence Day was made in 1994, the visual effects were stunning. The Matrix was made in 1999, the Visual Effects were stunning. A.I. Artificial Intelligence was made in 2001, the visual effects were stunning. <br> <br>

No offense to James Cameron, but that hardware is 1/100th the cost today. The time spent by artists creating those visuals we were told was a small fraction of the cost of the render farms. Why has it not already plummeted? Clearl</div>
