	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65297719"><p><div class="quote"><p>The blockbuster system is a horribly broken one -- you can make a good film people will love if they bother to watch it for $5m dollars, or make the same film with higher production values so you can get a larger watching audience (lots of people will turn off a film with low production values) for $30m.</p><p>Most modern films cost way more than that.</p></div><p>Lloyd Kaufman of Troma Studios (while bragging about 30 years without a single hit movie) explained Hollywood's obsession with big blockbusters very simply:</p><p>"You can't embezzle $10 million out of $5 million budget."</p></div>
