		<div id="comment_body_65298115"><p><div class="quote"><p>That's fine for an art festival, but general audiences are tired of it. They just want straightforward storytelling that makes you feel good when you come out of the theatre.</p></div><p>The success of the recent Deadpool film vs the rest of the "straight forward" by the numbers comic book hero stuff is a good counter point to your post. I don't think people are as dumb as you think. Bad writing is a problem, but not for the reasons you mention. Mainly for really fundamental stuff, like the kind of stuff you learn in 5th grade english *not to do* when writing a story.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65298115">

</div>
